<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>The Original Dulcimer Players Club (ODPC) was founded in 1963 by Elgia C. Hickok in Michigan.  The group aims to "promote and preserve the art of playing the Hammered Dulcimer."  Beginning in 1974, the ODPC has hosted a FunFest each summer at the Osceola County Fairgrounds in Evart, Michigan.  The event includes concerts, workshops, and informal jam sessions.  The event focuses on the hammered dulcimer, but other instruments are welcome as well (excluding band brass instruments, woodwind instruments with mechanical keys, most drums, and electrified instruments).</p>
</bioghist>

<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>The Original Dulcimer Players Club records document the group's organization and activities from its founding in 1963.  The records are arranged into six series: Administrative materials, Publications and events, Articles and newspaper clippings, Miscellaneous, Visual materials, and Audio materials. </p></scopecontent>

